<h4 id="trail-guide">Trail Guide</h4>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Duration</strong>: 1.5 miles, 55 minutes up; 35 down. (When very tired.)</li>
  <li><strong>Navigation</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Walk up-hill.  Follow the main road to the VORTAC</li>
      <li>At 1.2 miles, road makes a sharp left
        <ul>
          <li>At the sharp left, the AT can be reached via a short (100‚Äô) trail heading SW from the bend (behind the pole), and it parallels the road to the top.  It is 200‚Äô more walk, but nicer than walking the road.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>VORTAC at 1.3.  Follow the AT east about 0.1 to 35.7886,-83.05038, to avoid VORTAC QRM. Don‚Äôt activate near the VORTAC ‚Äì it is just an ugly space. If you walk 200‚Äô along the AT, there‚Äôs a nice camping spot with a lovely view of the mountains. (No shade.)</li>
      <li>Not only is the road too steep for 2WD, it is too steep to comfortably walk. In 2019, I started the walk feeling good and freshly caffeinated. By the time I reached the sharp left, where the steepness ends, I was resting after every few steps.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Trailhead altitude</strong>: ~3485‚Äô @ 35.7987,-83.0458 parking</li>
  <li><strong>Summit altitude</strong>: 4260‚Äô @ 35.7897, -83.0525</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="summit-guide">Summit Guide</h4>

<ul>
  <li>Hang antenna from tree: No.  Space to guy mast: Yes</li>
  <li>Cell coverage: <strong>2019</strong>: ATT yes; APRS unknown.</li>
</ul>
